From Eldon Tyrell Subject Re So what is the fastest Windows video c In article writes In article Amro Younes Trent University Peterborough ON Canada writes I have the ATI GRAPHICS ULTRA PRO EISA I must admit it has received bad press but that was due to the faulty drivers it PC Magazine seems to be impressed with the ATI card in their most recent In the April issue they rate the ATI Graphics Ultra Pro EISA version as their Editor's Choice They noted that the drivers had improved since they tested the ISA version in Yeah they also gave it their Editor's Choice in the run down of graphics accelerators they tested in the previous issue which is why I bought and then returned The only conclusion I can come up with is that PC Magazine has wildly different ways on determining the worthiness of a video card than I David Farley The University of Chicago Library East Street JRL Chicago Illinois